{
	"name": "Ivory Goats",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p>These ivory statuettes of goats are always created in sets of three. Each goat looks unique and functions differently from the others. Their properties are as follows:</p><p><strong>Goat of Terror.</strong></p><p><strong>Action</strong> - 3 Hours - 1/15 Days</p><p><strong>Summoning</strong></p><ul><li><p>The statue becomes a Large Construct using the<strong> @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-summoned-creatures.Actor.ObKuBjpo43uNbOVy]{Giant Goat}.</strong></p></li><li><p>This status can't attack, but you can (harmlessly) remove its horns and use them as weapons. One horn becomes a <em>+1 Lance</em> , and the other becomes a <em>+2 Longsword</em>. Removing a horn requires a Action, and the weapons disappear and the horns return when the goat reverts to figurine form.</p></li><li><p>While you ride the goat, any Hostile creature that starts its turn within a 30-foot Emanation originating from the goat must succeed on a [[/save wis 15]]{Wisdom Save (DC 15)} or become &amp;reference[Frightened] for 1 minute, until you are no longer riding the goat, or until the goat reverts to figurine form. The Frightened creature repeats the save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. Once it succeeds on the save, a creature is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours. Once the figurine has been used, it can't be used again until 15 days have passed.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Goat of Traveling</strong></p><p><strong>Action</strong> - 1 Hours - 24 Charges (7/Days)</p><p><strong>Summoning</strong></p><ul><li><p>1 Charge - This figurine becomes a Large Construct with the same statistics as a <strong>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.actors24.Actor.mmRidingHorse000]{Riding Horse} </strong>and looks like a Large Goat. Each hour or portion thereof it spends in goat form costs 1 charge. While it has charges, you can use it as often as you wish. When it runs out of charges, it reverts to a figurine and can't be used again until 7 days have passed, when it regains all expended charges.</p></li></ul><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-EI2OuwhLuEcOhXOQ\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>The <strong>Revert or Recall Goat of Traveling</strong> activity is optionally provided to aid in tracking the non-contiguous 24 hours the figurine can remain in goat form. When reverting to a figurine, the scaling value for consumption represents the number of hours spent in goat form. When recalling the figurine to goat form, uncheck the \"Consume Item Use?\" checkbox when using this activity.</p></section><p><strong>Goat of Travail</strong></p><p><strong>Action</strong> - 3 Hours - 1/30 Days</p><p><strong>Summoning</strong></p><ul><li><p>The statue becomes a Large Construct using the<strong> @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-summoned-creatures.Actor.ObKuBjpo43uNbOVy]{Giant Goat}.</strong></p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
